    "• Trivial Topics: Discovered topics are trivial with uninformative words.",
    "These topics cannot reveal the actual latent semantics of documents.",
    "As exemplified in Table 1, the topics include \"even\", \"just\", and \"really\".",
    "It is difficult to discern their underlying conceptual semantics.",
    "• Repetitive Topics: Discovered topics are repetitive with the same words, also referred to as the topic collapsing problem."
  ],
